<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 4:23PM CST  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Claiborne, southwestern Hinds and northwestern Copiah Counties
through 515 PM CST...
At 422 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Peyton, or 23 miles west of Hazlehurst, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Carpenter around 440 PM CST.
Dentville around 445 PM CST.
Utica around 450 PM CST.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
